'''''Backstreet Project''''' is an [[American comic book]] created by [[Nick Carter (musician)|Nick Carter]] and [[Stan Lee]]. The comic features members of Carter's band the [[Backstreet Boys]] as themselves as well as a team of superheroes called "Cyber Crusaders". The book was available for purchase at their concerts and online stores in 2000–2001.
==Publication history== Nick Carter, who was a comic fan, made an original concept of the comic planned as a six-issue series. In February 2000, he met Stan Lee through his manager from [[The Firm, Inc.|The Firm]]. Carter told him about his concept, and Lee was interested. However, they ultimately decided to make it into only one issue.<ref>{{cite book|title=Backstreet Project|year=2000|publisher=Stan Lee Media|page=30}}</ref>
==Plot== It begins when the Backstreet Boys are in the midst of one of their concerts. As they are performing on stage, a spaceship crashes near the stadium. The members rush into the woods to the crash site and there they find an alien who was on the ship. The alien gives each of them an enchanted amulet embedded with mystic crystals and they learn that she is on a mission of protecting Earth from an alien invasion that would happen soon. When they wear the amulets their DNA gets twisted by a virtual genetic cyclone that gives each of them astonishing super powers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.backstreetproject.com/story.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000817093928/http://www.backstreetproject.com/story.htm|archivedate=2000-08-17|title=Backstreet Project: Story Preview!|accessdate=2012-06-19}}</ref> The superhero form of the Backstreet Boys are called '''Cyber Crusaders'''.
