{{Infobox artist | bgcolour = | name = Daniel Dos Santos | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1978 | birth_place = [[Connecticut]]<ref name="tor">{{cite web|title=Artist Profile: Daniel Dos Santos |work=Tor.com |publisher=Tor.com |url=http://www.tor.com/bios/artists/dan-dossantos |accessdate=2014-08-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140828161413/http://www.tor.com/bios/artists/dan-dossantos |archivedate=2014-08-28 |df= }}</ref> | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = {{USA}} | field = | training = | movement = | works = | patrons = | influenced by = | influenced = | awards = [[Jack Gaughan Award]], [[Chesley Award]] | website = [http://www.dandossantos.com dandossantos.com] }}
'''Daniel Dos Santos''' (born 1978) is an American speculative fiction artist whose work has appeared on book covers by publishers [[Tor Books|Tor]], [[Bantam Books|Bantam]], [[Pyr (publisher)|Pyr]], and many more, as well as a variety of magazine and comic covers and interiors. He has been nominated for the [[Hugo Award]] seven times.
A love of comics led Dos Santos to an interest in art. During his final year of high school, he served an internship with [[Steven Stroud]].<ref name="greenwich">{{cite web | title = Daniel Dos Santos Biography | work = Greenwich Workshop| url = http://www.greenwichworkshop.com/dossantos/| accessdate = 2014-08-07}}</ref> Following graduation, he attended the [[School of Visual Arts]] in New York City, where he began to focus on speculative art.<ref name="tor" /> Dos Santos and Stroud founded a studio in [[Shelton, Connecticut]], after he graduated.<ref name="greenwich" />
Dos Santos, along with [[Irene Gallo]], has hosted a series of live art demonstrations at the [[Society of Illustrators]] in [[Manhattan]] called "Art Out Loud." The series began as a collaborative painting demo, but changed over time to better reflect the way in which artists actually work.<ref>{{cite web | title = Spotlight on Daniel Dos Santos, Artist | work = Locus Online | publisher = Locus | date = 2010-10-23 | url = http://www.locusmag.com/Perspectives/2010/10/spotlight-on-daniel-dos-santos-artist/ | accessdate = 2014-06-29}}</ref>
Dos Santos has been nominated for the [[Hugo Award for Best Professional Artist]] each year since 2009. Dos Santos received the Rhodes Family Award for special achievement in illustration in 2000, as well as the [[The Starr Foundation|Starr Foundation Award]] for 2001.<ref name="greenwich" /> He has received the 2007 [[Jack Gaughan Award]] for Best Emerging Artist and won the first [[Chesley Award for Best Cover Illustration – Paperback]] in the same year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bio |work=The Art of Dan Dos Santos |url=http://www.dandossantos.com/bio.htm |accessdate=2014-06-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130626062857/http://www.dandossantos.com/bio.htm |archivedate=2013-06-26 |df= }}</ref>
