{{Infobox television channel | name = Free TV | logofile = FreeTv Egypt Logo.png | logosize = 140 | logoalt = Logo used from July 2015 to December 2016 | logocaption = Logo used from July 2015 to December 2016. | launch = {{Start date and age|2015|7|20}} | picture format = [[576i]] '''[[SDTV]]''' | owner = [[Nasr Mahrous]] | slogan = ''& many many more…'' | country = [[Egypt]] | language = {{hlist|[[Arabic]]|[[English language|English]]|[[Spanish language|Spanish]]}} | broadcast area = {{ubl|[[North Africa]]|[[Middle East]]}} | headquarters = [[Cairo]], Egypt | website = {{URL|www.freetvmusic.tv}} | terr serv 1 = | terr chan 1 = | sat serv 1 = [[Nilesat]] (7°W) (Arab League) | sat chan 1 = 11900 V 27500 5/6 (SD)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://alnabaa.net/Story/454295|title=اليوم .. نصر محروس يُطلق قناة "فرى "تى فى|date=July 20, 2016|work=Al Nabaa|language=Arabic|access-date=December 19, 2016}}</ref> | cable serv 1 = | cable chan 1 = | iptv serv 1 = | iptv chan 1 = | online serv 1 = | online chan 1 = }}
'''Free TV''' ({{lang-ar|فري تي في}}), stylized as '''free{{sup|tv}}''', is a 24-hour pan-Arab musical television channel owned by [[Nasr Mahrous]] and headquartered in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]]. Its main target demographic is teenagers, high school and college students and young adults. It has special partnerships with [[Nasr Mahrous#FreeMusic Art Production|FreeMusic]], [[Universal Music Group]] and [[Sony Music]].<ref name="FB">{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/FreeTVMusic/about|title=Free TV – About|website=Facebook|language=Arabic|access-date=December 19, 2016}}</ref>
According to the channel's owner, it was planned that Free TV would be launched in the summer of 2014, however, it was introduced to the world in 2015, via [[Nilesat]].<ref name="bldna">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bldnaalyoum.com/10655|title=إنطلاق قناة "فرى تى فى" بعيد الفطر|last=|first=|date=May 25, 2015|work=Bldna Al Youm|language=Arabic|access-date=December 19, 2016|via=}}</ref> Nasr Mahrous said also that the name of the channel was chosen in order to be similar with "FreeMusic", the name of the record label he owns.<ref name="bldna" />
[[File:NasrMahrous2.jpg|thumb|[[Nasr Mahrous]], owner of the channel.]]
Its main objective is to combine different cultures through the language of entertainment, and to be a showcase of modern and classic Arab and international music blended together.
Free TV is rated on the top of the musical television channels in [[North Africa]] and the [[Middle East]], for providing an exclusive, outstanding and quality content of clips and programs, and creating awareness about new talents, songs and albums from all over the [[Arab world]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.youm7.com/story/2015/7/21/%D9%86%D8%B5%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3--%D9%85%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AC%D8%A2%D8%AA-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%87%D9%88%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%89-%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%89-%D9%81%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A8%D9%84%D8%A9/2273166#.VkC1E_krJdg|title=نصر محروس: مفاجآت للجمهور فى "فرى تى فى" الفترة المقبلة|date=July 21, 2015|work=Youm 7|language=Arabic|access-date=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.egypttoday.co.uk/breakingnews/%D9%86%D8%B5%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%D9%8A%D8%B7%D9%84%D9%82-%D9%82%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%89-%D9%81%D9%89.html|title=نصر محروس يطلق قناته الفضائية "فرى تى فى|date=May 25, 2015|work=Egypt Today|language=Arabic|access-date=December 19, 2016}}</ref>
== Programming == Free TV airs mainly western music videos of artists signed to [[Universal Music Group]] and [[Sony Music]],<ref name="FB" /> as well as many Arab music clips produced by [[Nasr Mahrous#FreeMusic Art Production|FreeMusic]] record label, that is also owned by [[Nasr Mahrous]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elfagr.org/1753725|title="فرى تى فى" قناة جديدة يطلقها المنتج نصر محروس|date=May 25, 2015|work=El Fagr|language=Arabic|access-date=December 19, 2016}}</ref> * ''Big Apple Music Awards'' * ''Free Mashup'' * ''Love Songs'' * ''The Mix''
